me="mat-mdc-button-ripple" jslog="185865;track:generic_click;BardVeMetadataKey:[[&quot;r_4b109c20bf57f112&quot;,&quot;c_bacbcc7396081285&quot;,null,&quot;rc_79cd40a505793a2a&quot;]];mutable:true" aria-describedby="cdk-describedby-message-ng-1-42" cdk-describedby-host="ng-1"><span class="mat-mdc-button-persistent-ripple mdc-button__ripple"></span><span class="mdc-button__label"><div _ngcontent-ng-c2687545729="" class="button-icon-wrapper"><!----><mat-icon _ngcontent-ng-c2687545729="" role="img" fonticon="download" class="mat-icon notranslate button-icon google-symbols mat-ligature-font mat-icon-no-color ng-star-inserted" aria-hidden="true" data-mat-icon-type="font" data-mat-icon-name="download"></mat-icon><!----><!----></div></span><!----><span class="mat-focus-indicator"></span><span class="mat-mdc-button-touch-target"></span></button><!----><!----><!----><mat-menu _ngcontent-ng-c2687545729="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----></mat-menu><!----></download-generated-image-button><!----></div><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></div><!----><!----></div><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></single-image></generated-image><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></response-element></div></p><p data-path-to-node="1">I have generated the premium branding assets for EliteMedBilling. Here are the logo variations that will be integrated into the final application, reflecting the navy blue and sky blue SaaS aesthetic we discussed:</p><ul data-path-to-node="2"><li><p data-path-to-node="2,0,0"><b data-path-to-node="2,0,0" data-index-in-node="0">Primary Horizontal Logo:</b> Features the shield icon, the bold "ELITE" and lighter "MedBilling" typography, and the "Revenue Cycle Management" tagline. This will be used in the main website header.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="2,1,0"><b data-path-to-node="2,1,0" data-index-in-node="0">Minimal Icon:</b> A standalone version of the shield and revenue cycle icon. This will be used as the browser favicon and mobile app icon.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="2,2,0"><b data-path-to-node="2,2,0" data-index-in-node="0">Emblem Badge:</b> A circular version that will be used in the footer and on physical branding materials.</p></li></ul><h3 data-path-to-node="3"><b data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="0">Final Confirmation Required</b></h3><p data-path-to-node="4">To ensure the backend logic and default content are accurate, I still require the following information from Part A before generating the code:</p><ol start="3" data-path-to-node="5"><li><p data-path-to-node="5,0,0"><b data-path-to-node="5,0,0" data-index-in-node="0">Contact Info:</b> Business Address, Phone Number, and Primary Contact Email for the footer and form notifications.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="5,1,0"><b data-path-to-node="5,1,0" data-index-in-node="0">SMTP Details:</b> Which provider (SendGrid, Resend, or standard SMTP) will be used for email notifications?</p></li></ol><p data-path-to-node="6"><b data-path-to-node="6" data-index-in-node="0">Once you provide these last two details, I will generate the complete, production-ready codebase.</b></p></div></message-content><!----></div></structured-content-container><!----><!----><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c4182224903="" class="response-footer contains-extensions-response gap complete"><!----><!----><!----><sources-list _ngcontent-ng-c4182224903="" class="sources-list ng-star-inserted"><!----></sources-list><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></div></div><!----><sensitive-memories-banner _ngcontent-ng-c4182224903="" _nghost-ng-c441501597="" cl