ments ng-star-inserted" _nghost-ng-c715347843="" style="height: auto;"><div _ngcontent-ng-c715347843="" class="container"><message-content _ngcontent-ng-c715347843="" _nghost-ng-c411533729="" id="message-content-id-r_86e38ac938d6308b" class="ng-star-inserted"><div _ngcontent-ng-c411533729="" inline-copy-host="" class="markdown markdown-main-panel enable-updated-hr-color" id="model-response-message-contentr_86e38ac938d6308b" aria-live="off" aria-busy="false" dir="ltr" style="--animation-duration: 400ms; --fade-animation-function: ease-out;"><p data-path-to-node="0">Excellent. Since we've finalized the visual identity with <b data-path-to-node="0" data-index-in-node="58">EliteMedBilling</b> (as seen in watermarked_img_17958641478171189224.png), I will proceed with the full technical architecture. I'll use placeholders for the contact details and SMTP settings which you can easily update via the <code data-path-to-node="0" data-index-in-node="282">.env</code> file or the Admin CMS.</p><hr data-path-to-node="1"><h2 data-path-to-node="2">🏗️ Project Structure: <code data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="23">elitemed-billing</code></h2><response-element class="" ng-version="0.0.0-PLACEHOLDER"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><code-block _nghost-ng-c3933017335="" class="ng-tns-c3933017335-53 ng-star-inserted" style=""><!----><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c3933017335="" class="code-block ng-tns-c3933017335-53 ng-animate-disabled ng-trigger ng-trigger-codeBlockRevealAnimation" jslog="223238;track:impression,attention;BardVeMetadataKey:[[&quot;r_86e38ac938d6308b&quot;,&quot;c_bacbcc7396081285&quot;,null,&quot;rc_20a46c112ef5fe2d&quot;,null,null,&quot;&quot;,null,1,null,null,1,0]]" data-hveid="0" decode-data-ved="1" data-ved="0CAAQhtANahcKEwiD7sa47-qTAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQWg" style="display: block;"><div _ngcontent-ng-c3933017335="" class="code-block-decoration header-formatted gds-title-s ng-tns-c3933017335-53 ng-star-inserted" style=""><span _ngcontent-ng-c3933017335="" cl